explanation: Dynamic programming approach with a helper function to calculate the cost of making a substring a semi-palindrome. The main DP table tracks the minimum cost for each prefix of the string and each number of partitions. The get_cost function calculates the minimum changes required to make a substring a semi-palindrome by counting the number of distinct characters at each position in the repeating pattern.

